{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567200","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567200"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:56:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:56:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18945"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18945","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18945"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.05,0.07,0.77,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11679"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80512"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11679","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11679"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18945"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65801"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5641"},{"type":"tags","id":"5642"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11259"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11281"},{"type":"tags","id":"11302"},{"type":"tags","id":"11393"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27481"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27492"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80512","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80512"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor is preparing their curriculum vitae for specialist training applications. They have received advice from colleagues about ways to make their application more competitive, including various strategies for presenting their achievements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe Medical Board guidelines state that practitioners must not engage in conduct that could mislead or deceive. The guidelines specifically note that this includes \u0027any material misrepresentation by omission or otherwise in relation to qualifications, experience, or professional activities\u0027.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following represents conduct that would NOT breach professional obligations regarding curriculum vitae preparation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Listing informal study sessions as teaching experience","Describing project participation as project leadership","Listing research as \u0027in press\u0027 before submission","Listing verified publications in peer-reviewed journals","Extending employment dates to cover career gaps"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe only acceptable approach is \u003Cstrong\u003Elisting verified publications in peer-reviewed journals\u003C/strong\u003E. This represents truthful documentation of actual achievements without misrepresentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe problematic approaches are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EListing informal study sessions as teaching experience\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003Cbr /\u003EThis misrepresents casual peer interactions as formal teaching roles, which could inflate perceived expertise.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescribing project participation as project leadership\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003Cbr /\u003EOverstating the level of responsibility or involvement creates a false impression of skills and experience.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EListing research as \u0027in press\u0027 before submission\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003Cbr /\u003EThis misrepresents the publication status. \u0022In press\u0022 specifically means the manuscript has been formally accepted by a journal, not merely intended for submission.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtending employment dates to cover career gaps\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003Cbr /\u003EAltering employment history is a clear falsification, breaching ethical standards.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProfessional integrity requires that all information provided must be not only technically true but also presented in a way that does not create misleading impressions. The obligation extends beyond avoiding direct falsehoods to include the duty to present a complete and accurate representation of one\u0027s professional history.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical registration boards consider falsification of qualifications or experience as serious professional misconduct that may result in disciplinary action.","The obligation for truthful representation extends beyond direct falsehoods to include misleading implications and strategic omissions.","Professional integrity in documentation is fundamental to maintaining public trust in the medical profession."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65801"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18945"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65801","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65801"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-21T11:12:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-21T11:13:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11679"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80512"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","lin